-- Macquarie Metals Analyst Lennon Said to Retire After 19 Years
-- B y   A g n i e s z k a   T r o s z k i e w i c z
-- 2013-05-30T17:23:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-05-30/macquarie-metals-analyst-lennon-said-to-retire-after-19-years.html
Jim Lennon, the chairman of
commodities research at  Macquarie Group Ltd. (MQG) , is retiring after
19 years and has been succeeded by Colin Hamilton, according to
two people with direct knowledge of the matter.  The bank’s commodities team was created by Lennon in 1994
and now consists of 11 staff in London, Shanghai and  Singapore ,
according to the people, who asked not to be identified because
the information isn’t public.  Lennon will continue to work as a consultant on metals and
mining, including part time with Macquarie, the people said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Agnieszka Troszkiewicz in London at 
